xM_x + yM_y = \frac{M}{N} (xN_x + yN_y) = f\Big(\frac{y}{x}\Big)(xN_x + yN_y )
M(x,y) = N(x,y) F(x,y)
x M_x + y M_y = x (N F)_x + y (N F)_y = (x N_x + y N_y) F + N (x F_x + y F_y)
F(x,y) = f(y/x)
F_x = - f'(y/x) \frac{y}{x^2}
F_y = \frac{f'(y/x)}{x}
x F_x + y F_y = 0
